            <!-- Recipes -->
            <div type="recipe">
               <head xml:id="jam_cake"><hi rend="sc">JAM CAKE</hi></head>
               <list>
                  <item n="1">3 eggs</item>
                  <item n="2">1 cup sugar</item>
                  <item n="3">¾ cup butter</item>
                  <item n="4">1½ cups flour</item>
                  <item n="5">1 cup jam</item>
                  <item n="6">3 tablespoons sour cream</item>
                  <item n="7">1 teaspoonful soda</item>
                  <item n="8">Spices of all kinds</item>
               </list>
               <byline><hi rend="sc"><persName>Alice Smith</persName></hi></byline>
            </div>

            <div type="recipe">
               <head xml:id="cocoanut_drops"><hi rend="sc">COCOANUT DROPS</hi></head>
               <list>
                  <item n="1">1 cup sugar</item>
                  <item n="2">1–3 cup hot water</item>
               </list>
               <p>Boil sugar and water until it forms a fine hair.</p>
               <!--should it be item or list?-->
               <p>1 lb. shredded cocoanut, 3–4 whites beaten stiff. Add syrup to beaten whites and
                  beat thoroughly, then stir in enough cocoanut to make the mixture very stiff. Mold
                  into balls about an inch thick. Bake on a buttered pan in a hot oven until a light
                  brown.</p>
               <byline><hi rend="sc"><persName>Dorothy Wade</persName></hi></byline>
            </div>

            <div type="recipe">
               <head xml:id="sponge_cake"><hi rend="sc">SPONGE CAKE</hi></head>
               <p>To two well beaten eggs, add 1 cup of sugar, ½ cup sifted flour. Stir well, then
                  add another ½ cup of flour with a teaspoonful of baking powder. Just before
                  putting in pan, add ½ cup of boiling water and flavor.</p>
               <byline><hi rend="sc"><persName>Ione Holmes</persName></hi></byline>
            </div>

            <div type="recipe">
               <head xml:id="wasington_pie"><hi rend="sc">WASHINGTON PIE</hi></head>
               <list>
                  <item n="1">1–3 cup butter</item>
                  <item n="2">1 cup sugar</item>
                  <item n="3">2 eggs</item>
                  <item n="4">½ cup milk</item>
                  <item n="5">1¾ cups flour</item>
                  <item n="6">2½ teaspoons baking powder</item>
               </list>
               <pb n="37"/>
               <p>Mix as one egg cake. Bake in round layer cake pans. Put jam or jelly between
                  layers and sprinkle top with powdered sugar.</p>
            </div>

            <div type="recipe">
               <head xml:id="christmas_honey_cake"><hi rend="sc">CHRISTMAS HONEY CAKE</hi></head>
               <list>
                  <item n="1">1½ cups citron and almond nuts chopped fine</item>
                  <item n="2">2 cups brown sugar</item>
                  <item n="3">3 eggs</item>
                  <item n="4">3 cups flour</item>
                  <item n="5">2 tablespoons honey</item>
                  <item n="6">1½ teaspoons soda</item>
                  <item n="7">1 teaspoon cloves</item>
                  <item n="8">½ teaspoon allspice</item>
                  <item n="9">½ teaspoon cinnamon</item>
                  <item n="10">½ teaspoon ginger</item>
                  <item n="11">¼ teaspoon nutmeg</item>
               </list>
               <p>Beat yolks and whites of eggs separately. Add sugar to the yolks, then add honey,
                  flour, and the soda dissolved in a little hot water. Fold in the whites of eggs
                  and add spices and nuts. Bake in sheets and cut in triangles. Ice with thin
                  frosting made of sugar and water.</p>
               <byline><hi rend="sc"><persName>Mamie Cameron</persName></hi></byline>
            </div>

            <div type="recipe">
               <head xml:id="one_egg_cake"><hi rend="sc">ONE-EGG CAKE</hi></head>
               <list>
                  <item n="1">1 cup sugar</item>
                  <item n="2">1 large tablespoon butter</item>
                  <item n="3">1 egg</item>
                  <item n="4">1½ cups flour</item>
                  <item n="5">½ cup sweet milk</item>
                  <item n="6">2 teaspoonfuls baking powder</item>
                  <item n="7">1 teaspoonful vanilla</item>
               </list>
               <p>Cream the butter and sugar. Add beaten egg, mix in milk and flour slowly.</p>
               <byline><hi rend="sc"><persName>Catherine Baxter</persName></hi></byline>
            </div>

            <div type="recipe">
               <head xml:id="nut_loaf"><hi rend="sc">NUT LOAF</hi></head>
               <list>
                  <item n="1">1½ cups white flour</item>
                  <item n="2">1½ cups graham flour</item>
                  <item n="3">½ cup molasses</item>
                  <item n="4">Pinch of salt</item>
                  <item n="5">¾ cup nut meats</item>
                  <item n="6">2 teaspoonfuls baking powder</item>
               </list>
               <p>Sweet milk to make soft but not thin. Let stand for ½ hour. Bake slowly in bread
                  pan from ½ to ¾ hour.</p>
            </div>

            <pb n="38"/>
            <div type="recipe">
               <head xml:id="sour_cream_cookies"><hi rend="sc">SOUR CREAM COOKIES</hi></head>
               <p>Mix together 2 cups sugar, ½ cup butter, 2 eggs well beaten, ½ cup sour milk, ½
                  teaspoonful cinnamon and ½ teaspoonful cloves and soda. Drop by spoonfuls on
                  buttered tins.</p>
            </div>

            <div type="recipe">
               <head xml:id="walnut_chocolates"><hi rend="sc">WALNUT CHOCOLATES</hi></head>
               <list>
                  <item n="1">Whites of 3 eggs</item>
                  <item n="2">¾ cup granulated sugar</item>
                  <item n="3">¾ cup Baker’s grated chocolate</item>
                  <item n="4">1 cup chopped walnut</item>
               </list>
               <p>Beat eggs until very stiff. Add sugar gradually; then chocolate and nuts. Drop in
                  small teaspoonfuls on buttered paper. Bake in a moderate oven.</p>
               <byline><hi rend="sc"><persName>Martha Davis</persName></hi></byline>
            </div>

            <div type="recipe">
               <head xml:id="rich_chocolate_cake"><hi rend="sc">RICH CHOCOLATE CAKE</hi></head>
               <list>
                  <item n="1">1 ¾ cups sugar</item>
                  <item n="2">15 tablespoons butter</item>
                  <item n="3">3 eggs</item>
                  <item n="4">1 ½ cups flour</item>
                  <item n="5">2 teaspoons baking powder</item>
                  <item n="6">¼ lb. chocolate</item>
                  <item n="7">1 tablespoons cocoa</item>
                  <item n="8">1 teaspoon vanilla</item>
               </list>
               <p>Cream butter, add sugar gradually–yolks of eggs beaten light, melt chocolate and
                  cocoa, milk and flour (sifted with baking powder alternately) —whites of eggs
                  beaten stiff and vanilla. Bake one hour in moderate oven. </p>
               <byline><hi rend="sc"><persName>Miss E. I. Raitt</persName></hi></byline>
            </div>

            <div type="recipe">
               <head xml:id="rocks"><hi rend="sc">ROCKS</hi></head>
               <list>
                  <item n="1">½ c. brown sugar</item>
                  <item n="2">1 c. butter</item>
                  <item n="3">3 eggs beaten separately</item>
                  <item n="4">1 ½ c. raisins chopped fine</item>
                  <item n="5">2 ½ c. flour</item>
                  <item n="6">1 tsp. soda, dissolved in hot water</item>
                  <item n="7">1 tsp. cinnamon</item>
                  <item n="8">1 tsp. Vanilla</item>
               </list>
               <p>Drop from spoon into buttered pans. This will make fifty cakes.</p>
            </div>

